	url = {https://dl.acm.org/doi/10.1145/3763114},
	doi = {10.1145/3763114},
	shorttitle = {Choreographic Quick Changes},
	abstract = {Choreographic programming is a promising new paradigm for programming concurrent systems where a developer writes a single centralized program that compiles to individual programs for each node. Existing choreographic languages, however, lack critical features integral to modern systems, like the ability of one node to dynamically compute who should perform a computation and send that decision to others. This work addresses this gap with λ
              
