              , the first typed choreographic language with
              first class process names
              and polymorphism over both types and (sets of) locations. λ
              
                {QC}
              
              also improves expressive power over previous work by supporting algebraic and recursive data types as well as multiply-located values. We formalize and mechanically verify our results in Rocq, including the standard choreographic guarantee of deadlock freedom.},
	pages = {1783--1808},
	issue = {{OOPSLA}2},
	journaltitle = {Proceedings of the {ACM} on Programming Languages},
	shortjournal = {Proc. {ACM} Program. Lang.},
	author = {Samuelson, Ashley and Hirsch, Andrew K. and Cecchetti, Ethan},
	urldate = {2025-10-21},
	date = {2025-10-09},
	langid = {english},
}

